#trying to write a function to make this thing take up less lines

tidy_pls <- function(x, print = TRUE){
    no.top <- x[7:31,]
  library(reshape2)
    transposed <- t(no.top)
    tidy.sub <- data.frame(rbind(transposed[-1, 1:5], transposed[-1, 7:11], transposed[-1, 15:19], transposed[-1, 21:25]))
    colnames(tidy.sub) <- c("site", "PD", "BOP", "GM.CEJ", "CAL")
    tidy.sub$date.raw <- x[2,2]
    tidy.sub$data.recorder <- x[3,2]
    tidy.sub$clinician <- x[4,2]
    #############################
    tidy.sub$aim <- "SA3"
    #CHANGE THE ABOVE THING LATER
    
    return(tidy.sub)
}

  #i think this function only works for very specific things like finding the CAL for this specific type of dataset. If the class of certain things were changed around, then this function would probably not work anymore

      num2 <- as.numeric(as.vector(x$GM.CEJ))
      val2 <- sum(num2[complete.cases(num2)])
